import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby(['Year', 'Entity']).sum().reset_index()
    
    for disaster_type in data['Entity'].unique():
        subset = data[data['Entity'] == disaster_type]
        plt.plot(subset['Year'], subset['Deaths'], label=disaster_type)
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Deaths')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the trend of natural disasters over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    grouped_data = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    ax = grouped_data.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Which type of natural disaster has caused the most deaths?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['Deaths'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Deaths')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths caused by natural disasters?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    median_deaths = data['Deaths'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_deaths, color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median Deaths: {median_deaths:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
